						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the <hi rend="italic">mahā-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Tiruppālēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Kāḷayukti, Māgha ba. 2.</p>						

						<p>Records the construction of a <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> by Peddarāja, son of Ōbaḷrājayya of Kōḷūru. In characters of the 18th century A.D. The donor is given some of the titles that appear in the inscription no. 5 above.</p>						

